      "side": 1,
      "message": "As per discussed earlier, reveman@ mentioned that we could possibly grab the mouse events, and always use EV_REL mouse events which matches the real mouse hardware better.\n\nIn that case we could send relx and rely directly to kbd_mouse_event().\n\nOne problem is that, QEMU\u0027s kbd_mouse_event() determines input type from device HID descriptor, while the input source may send anything (they may send an ABS location or a REL location); my suggestion is that we also pass the event type (ABS or REL) to kbd_mouse_event() so that it will only forward the correct type of event to virtio. I\u0027ve just added a TODO for that and will address it soon.",
